    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following best describes the advantage of using hydrofluorocarbons (<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H F Cs\"><math alttext=\"H F Cs\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>HFCs</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>) or hydrochlorofluorocarbons (<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H C F Cs\"><math alttext=\"H C F Cs\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>HCFCs</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>) to replace chlorofluorocarbons (<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C F Cs\"><math alttext=\"C F Cs\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>CFCs</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>) in industrial processes?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
